<a name="Apps">
<h2> WHAT ARE SCRAWL APPS? </h2>
</a>
<p></b>
Scrawl apps are little programs you work with to put scrawl on a web page.  So scrawl apps can do many different things:
<ul>
	<li>
		They can be as simple as clip art that are just dropped onto the page at the desired location.
	<li>
		They can be more sophisticated, such as the 'dislike button' or apps for changing and marking up photos.
</ul>
<br />
<h4> SOME SCRAWL APPS </h4>
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Speech Balloon	:	type what you want in it</li>
	<li>Thought Balloon	:	with audio clips you can play back</li>
	<li>Dislike Button  :	just like the 'like' button, but more fun </li>
	<li>Photo Blaster	:	put headers or footers on photos in the gallery</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h4> HOW DO APPS WORK? </h4>
</a>
</p></b>
All apps do the same thing in different ways.  They put content onto the page.  The content may be simple, like clip art, or more complicated, like a thought balloon with audio and it may only be allowed in certain places, like a profile picture, or it may be allowed anywhere on the page, but it all comes down to putting content on the page.
